Nerd Fonts Symbols (curated subset embedded in syscons)
=======================================================

This directory embeds monochrome bitmap glyphs rasterized from:

  Nerd Fonts "Symbols Only" — SymbolsNerdFontMono-Regular.ttf
  Package: nerd-fonts (SymbolsOnly)
  Upstream: https://github.com/ryanoasis/nerd-fonts

The Symbols Only distribution is labeled MIT:

  Copyright (c) 2014 Ryan L McIntyre
  MIT License (see NerdFontsSymbolsOnly/LICENSE on the host font package)

Nerd Fonts aggregates glyphs from many FOSS icon fonts (MIT, SIL OFL 1.1,
Apache-2.0, etc.). Those component licenses permit redistribution and use
in FreeBSD/DragonFly-style BSD systems when attribution is preserved.

Embed policy (S2):
  - BMP private-use / symbol ranges through Font Awesome legacy band
    (approximately U+E000–U+F2FF plus a few misc symbols), monochrome
    16x32 bitmaps only — not the full TTF and not the plane-1 mega set.
  - Bitmaps are derived works (rasterizations).
  - This NOTICE must be retained when redistributing the kernel image
    or source that includes font_ext_nerd16x32.h.

BSD compatibility: MIT and OFL/Apache icon sources used by Nerd Fonts are
generally compatible with 2/3-clause BSD distribution of a larger work
(kernel). Do NOT add icon sets that are proprietary or NC-only.

Regenerate:
  python3 scripts/raster_nerd_symbols.py --profile s2

Mono emoji subset (S3)
----------------------
Bitmaps also derived from Google Noto Color Emoji, licensed under the
SIL Open Font License 1.1 (see host package noto-emoji OFL11). Rasterized
to monochrome 32x32 and split into 16x32 cell halves for the console.
Regenerate: python3 scripts/raster_emoji_mono.py --max-glyphs 400

Spleen Unicode + letter fill
----------------------------
Additional monochrome glyphs extracted from Spleen 16x32 BDF (BSD-2-Clause,
Frederic Cambus). Gaps in Greek/Cyrillic/Latin-Extended filled from
DejaVu Sans Mono (Bitstream Vera / Arev free fonts).

Non-CJK multi-script letters (Spleen Unicode + Noto/DejaVu fill)
----------------------------------------------------------------
font_ext_letters16x32.h embeds:
  - Spleen 16x32 BDF Unicode above U+00FF (BSD-2-Clause)
  - Gap fill rasterized from DejaVu Sans Mono and Noto Sans* families
    (OFL-1.1 / Bitstream Vera free licenses), excluding CJK blocks.
Hebrew/Arabic/Indic/etc. are isolated glyphs only (no bidi or shaping).
